<TITLE> Long-haul bus fare cut </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 23 (bdnews24.com)  The government has decided to cut bus fare for long distance route by Tk 0.02 per kilometre in the awake of fuel price fall. The communications ministry in a statement said on Tuesday the fare of bus run on diesel was made Tk 0.96 from Tk 0.98 per kilometre. The fare for the diesel-run buses on Mawa-Paturia route through ferry terminal was set Tk 0.99. The present rate of the buses is Tk 1.01 per kilometre. The fare of diesel-run minibus was set at Tk 0.99 from Tk 1.01 and rate for the minibuses on Mawa-Paturia route through ferry terminal was set Tk 1.02 from Tk 1.04. The decision will be made effective immediately, the statement said. The fuel price cuts, announced by the government on Monday, came into force at midnight. The price of diesel and kerosene came down from Tk 48 to Tk 46, petrol from Tk 78 to Tk 74, and octane from Tk 80 to Tk 77, according to a government circular. bd
